      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE NITESHIFT (10) has shown good ability in winning his two starts to date including a 14m romp at this circuit and distance on debut. Up in grade and starts from the outside barrier but overcame a second row draw in scoring last time at Penrith and has been kept up to the mark with a solid trial since. COCOS DESIRE (9) draws wider but did a hob in a last-start win over a handy filly at this circuit and distance. She has more upside than most of these. STEEL STRIDE (8) is also drawn deep but has been producing some decent efforts including a Canberra win three back. Go well. VESPA STRIDE (5) is up in grade but has been racing very well, putting together a string of top-two finishes at this circuit and distance.",
